The paper discusses the application of machine learning methods to drug design and discovery, specifically focusing on the learning of quantitative structure activity relationships (QSARs). This falls under the category of machine learning, which is covered by cs.LG. Additionally, the paper discusses algorithm selection and the comparison of different machine learning methods, which are topics that are often studied in the sub-categories of computational engineering (cs.CE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper also touches on the societal importance of drug discovery, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
